# Contributor Covenant Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

We pledge to make participation in the Order 66 community a welcoming, respectful, and harassment-free experience for everyone.

## Our Standards

Positive behavior includes:

* Being respectful and professional.
* Providing constructive feedback.
* Helping contributors learn and grow.
* Collaborating openly and respectfully.
* Supporting the project and community.

Unacceptable behavior includes:

* Harassment, discrimination, or hateful conduct.
* Personal attacks and intimidation.
* Trolling or disruptive behavior.
* Publishing private information without permission.
* Any conduct that creates a hostile environment.

## Enforcement Responsibilities

Project maintainers are responsible for enforcing community standards and may remove content or restrict participation when necessary.

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces, including issues, pull requests, discussions, and community channels.

## Enforcement

Instances of unacceptable behavior may be reported to the project maintainers for review and appropriate action.

